para.verbatim: Child classes must define this method, which defines how the ``default_name`` is set.

Requires all given :class:`ParseExpression` s to be found in the given order. Expressions may be separated by whitespace. May be constructed using the ``'+'`` operator. May also be constructed using the ``'-'`` operator, which will suppress backtracking.
Example::
integer = Word(nums) name_expr = Word(alphas)[1, ...]
expr = And([integer("id"), name_expr("name"), integer("age")]) # more easily written as: expr = integer("id") + name_expr("name") + integer("age")
